<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9475&amp;p=104666#p104666"><![CDATA[
Two complaints I have:<br /><br />1) When going back to the level select the cursor is back to the first level, so in order to go to the next one you need to smash the ↓ button several times, which gets annoying. It would be better if the cursor was placed back in the last level that was played.<br /><br />2) Level 7 is ambiguous. Both of these solutions are valid (only the first one is acknowledged by the game):<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">X . . . X<br />. X . X .<br />. . X . .<br />. X . X .<br />X . . . X</div><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">. X . X .<br />X . . . X<br />. . X . .<br />X . . . X<br />. X . X .<br /></div>There are other combinations by mixing the different quarters from those two (for a grand total of 16), but you get the idea.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4526">Sik</a> — Thu Dec 13, 2012 5:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
